## Best Practices by Version

### Next.js 15.5.3 or --latest
- ✅ Use App Router (not Pages Router)
- ✅ Leverage Server Components when possible
- ✅ Implement Streaming for better UX
- ⚠️ Be careful with unnecessary Client Components

### React 19.1.1 or --latest
- ✅ Use React Compiler when available
- ✅ Leverage use() hook for promises
- ✅ Implement Suspense boundaries
- ⚠️ Avoid useEffect for data fetching (use React Query)

### TypeScript 5.9.2 or --latest
- ✅ Enable strict mode in tsconfig.json
- ✅ Use satisfies operator for type inference
- ✅ Implement branded types for IDs
- ⚠️ Avoid any, use unknown when necessary

### Redux Toolkit 2.9.0 or --latest
- ✅ Use createSlice for reducers
- ✅ Implement RTK Query for API calls
- ✅ Use createAsyncThunk for async actions
- ⚠️ Avoid direct state mutations

### React Query 3.39.3 or --latest
- ✅ Configure QueryClient with appropriate defaults
- ✅ Use useQuery for GET requests
- ✅ Use useMutation for POST/PUT/DELETE
- ⚠️ Implement error boundaries for queries

### Styled Components 6.1.19 or --latest
- ✅ Use ThemeProvider for design system
- ✅ Implement styled-components babel plugin
- ✅ Use CSS prop for dynamic styles
- ⚠️ Avoid unnecessary styled components

## Code Patterns

### Component Structure
```typescript
// ✅ Good example
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  onAction: () => void;
}

export const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({ title, onAction }) => {
  return <div onClick={onAction}>{title}</div>;
};
```

### Custom Hooks
```typescript
// ✅ Good example
export const useProduct = (id: string) => {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['product', id],
    queryFn: () => fetchProduct(id),
    enabled: !!id
  });
};
```

### Error Handling
```typescript
